content.problemStatement:
The `goto` statement allows you to transfer control to a labeled statement in your program - allowing non-linear program flow.. \
Sample syntax as follows
```c
#include 

int main() {
    int n = 10;
    int target = 5;

    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        printf("Iteration %d\n", i);

        if (i == target) {
            goto end;
        }
    }
    end:
    printf("Loop ended at iteration %d\n", target);
    return 0;
}
```
**Note:** Use sparingly and judiciously!!!

### Task
Take user provided integer inputs $N$ and $K$. \
It is known that $K \lt N$. \
You need to print numbers from 1 to $N$ except $K$.

